unittitle_ssm: MacDowell Club of New York City records
abstract_ssm: This collection includes minute books, scrapbooks, and other records of the MacDowell Club of New York City (1906-1945), founded in honor of composer Edward MacDowell to foster appreciation of the fine arts. The club played a significant role in the artistic life of the city in the first half of the 20th century.
